        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 18 at 8:24PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 824 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from near Rodessa to 8 miles southeast of
Hallsville, or extending from 17 miles southeast of Atlanta to 10
miles southwest of Marshall, moving southeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Shreveport, Bossier City, Marshall, Springhill, Vivian,
Hallsville, Greenwood, Blanchard, Waskom, Benton, Plain Dealing,
Oil City, Mooringsport, Hosston, Rodessa, Belcher, Ida, Gilliam,
Karnack and Smithland.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
